H0.text: lb is not an SI unit for density.

H1.text: kg is an SI unit for density.

H2.text: lb/ft^3 is an SI unit for density.

H3.text: kg/m³ is an SI unit for density.

A4.text: The SI unit of kilogram per cubic metre (kg/m3) and the cgs unit of gram per cubic centimetre (g/cm3) are probably the most commonly used units for density.

A5.text: In US customary units density can be stated in: pound per cubic foot (1 g/cm3 ≈ 62.427961 lb/cu ft).
